data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

In .NET 10, the Cosmos DB provider allowed you to opt into sync-over-async execution (typically via `ConfigureWarnings` suppressing `CosmosEventId.SyncNotSupported`). **In .NET 11, that opt-in is removed entirely.** All synchronous LINQ operators and `SaveChanges()` on the Cosmos provider now throw `InvalidOperationException` unconditionally.

Every method in your repository breaks:

| Call | Why it fails |
|------|-------------|
| `ToList()` | Sync enumeration removed |
| `First(...)` | Sync enumeration removed |
| `Count()` | Sync enumeration removed |
| `SaveChanges()` | Sync persist removed |

## Fix: convert to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

All callers up the stack must also become `async`/`await`. There is no supported synchronous path for the Cosmos provider in EF Core 11.
